# How to Add an Article to the Insights Page

Edit `articles.json` in GitHub to add, remove, or reorder articles.
Netlify deploys automatically within ~30 seconds of each commit.

---

## Adding an article

1. Go to your GitHub repo and open `articles.json`
2. Click the pencil icon (Edit this file)
3. Copy the block below and paste it **at the top of the array**, right after the opening `[`
4. Fill in your details
5. Click **Commit changes**

```json
{
  "title": "Your article title as published",
  "url": "https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/your-article-url",
  "source": "LinkedIn",
  "date": "May 2026",
  "excerpt": "One or two sentences summarising the article.",
  "tag": "Data Governance"
},
```

> **Note:** Every entry except the last one needs a comma after the closing `}`.

---

## Field reference

| Field     | Required | Notes                                              |
|-----------|----------|----------------------------------------------------|
| `title`   | Yes      | The article title as it appears on LinkedIn        |
| `url`     | Yes      | Full URL including `https://`                      |
| `source`  | No       | `LinkedIn`, `Published`, `Article`, or `Other`     |
| `date`    | No       | Free text — e.g. `May 2026` or `Feb 19, 2026`     |
| `excerpt` | No       | Short description shown under the title on the card |
| `tag`     | No       | Topic label — e.g. `Organizational Intelligence`   |

---

## Removing an article

Delete its entire `{ ... }` block from the array. Make sure no trailing comma
is left on the entry above it.

## Reordering articles

Articles display in the order they appear in the file — top of the array
shows first on the page. Cut and paste entries to reorder.
